  <sec sec-type="data-availability" id="da0010">
    <title>Data and code availability</title>
    <p id="p0030">
      <list list-type="simple" id="ulist0015">
        <list-item id="u0030">
          <label>•</label>
          <p id="p0035">This paper analyzes existing and publicly available data. All the datasets used and generated in our study were deposited in Zenodo (<ext-link ext-link-type="uri" xlink:href="https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7236202" id="intref0010">https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7236202</ext-link>) and they are publicly available as of the date of publication. Datasets include supplementary <xref rid="mmc2" ref-type="supplementary-material">Data S1. Marker genes of two chimpanzee organoids specific clusters, related to Figure 3</xref>, <xref rid="mmc3" ref-type="supplementary-material">Data S2. Differentially expressed genes within excitatory neurons of human brains or organoids, related to Figure 5</xref>, <xref rid="mmc4" ref-type="supplementary-material">Data S3. 1,533 human brain development-related genes, related to STAR Methods</xref> from this work.</p>
        </list-item>
        <list-item id="u0035">
          <label>•</label>
          <p id="p0040">All original codes have been deposited in Zenodo (<ext-link ext-link-type="uri" xlink:href="https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7556083" id="intref0015">https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7556083</ext-link>) and are also publicly available at GitHub (<ext-link ext-link-type="uri" xlink:href="https://github.com/daifengwanglab/BOMA" id="intref0020">https://github.com/daifengwanglab/BOMA</ext-link>). A web app of BOMA is available at <ext-link ext-link-type="uri" xlink:href="http://daifengwanglab.org/boma-webapp/" id="intref0025">http://daifengwanglab.org/boma-webapp/</ext-link>.</p>
        </list-item>
        <list-item id="u0040">
          <label>•</label>
          <p id="p0045">Any additional information required to reanalyze the data reported in this paper is available from the <xref rid="sec4.2.1" ref-type="sec">lead contact</xref> upon request.</p>
        </list-item>
      </list>
    </p>
  </sec>
